quran[30]{c,v,t,f}:
  68,40,"Ask them which of them, for that [claim], is responsible."
  68,41,"Or do they have partners?{1} Then let them bring their partners, if they should be truthful.",footnotes:1:i.e., those to whom they attribute divinity other than Allāh or partners from among themselves.
  68,42,"The Day the shin will be uncovered{1} and they are invited to prostration but they [i.e., the disbelievers] will not be able,",footnotes:1:i.e., when everyone will find before him great difficulty.  In accordance with authentic ḥadīths, "the shin" might also refer to that of Allāh (subḥānahu wa taʿālā), before which every believer will prostrate on the Day of Judgement.  See footnote to 2:19.
  69,37,"None will eat it except the sinners."
  69,38,"So I swear by what you see"
  69,39,"And what you do not see"
  70,31,"But whoever seeks beyond that, then they are the transgressors -"
  70,32,"And those who are to their trusts and promises attentive."
  70,33,"And those who are in their testimonies upright"
  71,28,"My Lord, forgive me and my parents and whoever enters my house a believer and the believing men and believing women. And do not increase the wrongdoers except in destruction."
  72,25,"Say, "
  72,26,"[He is] Knower of the unseen, and He does not disclose His [knowledge of the] unseen to anyone"
  72,27,"Except whom He has approved of messengers, and indeed, He sends before him [i.e., each messenger] and behind him observers{1}",footnotes:1:Guardian angels to protect the messenger and the message.
  73,19,"Indeed, this is a reminder, so whoever wills may take to his Lord a way."
  73,20,"Indeed, your Lord knows, [O Muḥammad], that you stand [in prayer] almost two thirds of the night or half of it or a third of it, and [so do] a group of those with you. And Allāh determines [the extent of] the night and the day. He has known that you [Muslims] will not be able to do it{1} and has turned to you in forgiveness, so recite what is easy [for you] of the Qur’ān. He has known that there will be among you those who are ill and others traveling throughout the land seeking [something] of the bounty of Allāh and others fighting for the cause of Allāh. So recite what is easy from it and establish prayer and give zakāh and loan Allāh a goodly loan.{2} And whatever good you put forward for yourselves - you will find it with Allāh. It is better and greater in reward. And seek forgiveness of Allāh. Indeed, Allāh is Forgiving and Merciful.",footnotes:1:Allāh has known that if they were to continue in such long periods of worship each night, the people would be caused much hardship.,footnotes:2:In the form of charities and contributions to His cause.
  74,16,"No! Indeed, he has been toward Our verses obstinate."
  74,17,"I will cover him with arduous torment."
  74,18,"Indeed, he thought and deliberated.{1}",footnotes:1:About what he would say concerning the Qur’ān and how he might discredit the Prophet (ﷺ).
  75,13,"Man will be informed that Day of what he sent ahead{1} and kept back.{2}",footnotes:1:i.e., his deeds, which await him in the Hereafter.,footnotes:2:i.e., that which he did not do or which he delayed.
  75,14,"Rather, man, against himself, will be a witness,{1}",footnotes:1:As described in 36:65 and 41:20-23.
  75,15,"Even if he presents his excuses."
  76,7,"They [are those who] fulfill [their] vows and fear a Day whose evil will be widespread."
  76,8,"And they give food in spite of love for it{1} to the needy, the orphan, and the captive,",footnotes:1:The meaning here may also be "out of love for Him," i.e., Allāh (subḥānahu wa taʿālā).
  76,9,"[Saying], "
  77,4,"And those [angels] who bring criterion{1}",footnotes:1:To Allāh's human messengers.
  77,5,"And those [angels] who deliver a message."
  77,6,"As justification or warning,"
  78,1,"About what are they asking one another?"
  78,2,"About the great news{1} -",footnotes:1:i.e., the Resurrection.
  78,3,"That over which they are in disagreement."